description: From the past participle stem of Latin īnsufflāre, from in- + sufflāre (“blow on”).

verbs.description: insufflate (third-person singular simple present insufflates, present participle insufflating, simple past and past participle insufflated)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To breathe or blow into or on.
(transitive, medicine) To treat by blowing a gas, vapor, or powder into a body cavity.
(transitive, ecclesiastical) To exhale upon baptismal water, or the one being baptised, as a ritual act.
